channel.title: Windows Varribles are Screwd
channel.description: I am trying to find out my local ip so i can port foward. I go to Cmd, type ipconfig, but im gettin is not recongized. It worked fine before. Same with the varrible java, which runs the server. Now i neeed to put C: and so on. I installed mysql recently, and that varribgle still works. Whats wrong?

item.title: Windows Varribles are Screwd
item.dc:creator: @eczema3 eczema3
item.description:
@eczema3 wrote:

I had the same problem with my cmd, something had stolen it and replaced it with a copy of it that didn’t work :\ so whenever i wanted t run cmd i jsut did start>run>C:\WINDOWS\system32\cmd.exe and it worked fine.

item.title: Windows Varribles are Screwd
item.dc:creator: @jme jme
item.description:
@jme wrote:

You might have screwed your path variable. Add: %SystemRoot%\system32;%SystemRoot%;%SystemRoot%\Sy stem32\wbem

If theres anything else in it, just put a semicolon after it, and add the above^
